Nomura Holdings Inc. (8604)  hired Vishal
Sodha to head bond, loan and distressed debt sales in the Asia-
Pacific region outside of  Japan , Hong Kong-based Sodha said when
contacted today on his mobile phone.  Sodha was previously with  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  where he
was head of credit sales for  Asia , he said. Sodhaâ€™s title at
Nomura will be managing director, heading credit flow and
illiquid sales, he said.  He will start with the Japanese investment bank in June and
will report to Singapore-based Samir Bhandari and Hong Kong-
based George Sun, co-heads of fixed-income sales for Asia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
